S-American media sphere.  afunded by Universität Koblenz-Landau  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aCulture. 0aHuman comfort. 0aQuality of life. 0aWell-being. 4aCultural History. 4aCultural Studies. 4aCultural Theory. 4aCulture. 4aFilm. 4aLiterary Studies. 4aLiterature. 4aMedia. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Popular Culture.2bisacsh  aCultural History.  aCultural Studies.  aCultural Theory.  aCulture.  aFilm.  aLiterary Studies.  aLiterature.  aMedia.1 aBirke, Dorothee, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBirke, Dorothee, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBreidbach, Angela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aButler, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aButter, Stella, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aButter, Stella, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBułat Silva, Zuzanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarandina, Elisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLiedke, Heidi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aListon, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarx, Dorothee, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMelcer-Padon, Nourit, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSezer, Burak, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStrick, Simon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSträtz, Juliane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTsangue Douanla, Didymus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb2 aUniver